citeinfo.othercit: This metadata record is a template for data created using the U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) Digital Shoreline Analysis System (DSAS) version 6.0 application. Basic process steps and attribute fields have been described but many required fields have been left blank for the DSAS user to enter their specifications. Therefore, this metadata file is not FGDC-compliant as is. The Digital Shoreline Analysis System (version 6) is a desktop application that loads GeoJSON files saved by a Geographic Information System. The DSAS software requires users to import a reference baseline and a set of shoreline positions. DSAS will then generate measurement transects and shoreline intersections which it will use to calculate rate-of-change statistics. In addition, DSAS provides uncertainties associated with rates of change. This metadata file accompanies a transect file of the same name that was created using the Digital Shoreline Analysis System version 6.0.

dataqual.logic: These data were generated using DSAS, an automated software program which does not perform checks for fidelity of the input features. Any testing on these data should be carried out by end-users to ensure fidelity of relationships.
dataqual.complete: This dataset contains all the transects automatically generated by the DSAS version 6 application. Incomplete fields in the metadata record should be updated by the DSAS user.

procstep.procdesc: Transect features generated using DSAS version 6.0.170. Parameters Used: baseline layer=baseline_stleu, transect spacing=50, transect length=200, baseline placement=true, smoothing distance=500

enttyp.enttypd: Transects were automatically generated by DSAS at a 90 degree angle to the user-specified baseline using a user-specified smoothing algorithm to maintain roughly parallel transects that are orthogonal with respect to the baseline. Transects are returned as a GeoJSON file.
enttyp.enttypds: U.S. Geological Survey, Woods Hole Science Center

attrdomv.udom: Unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Unique identification number of the baseline segment. If BaselineID=0 no transects will be generated. Used by DSAS to determine transect ordering alongshore if multiple baseline segments exist.
attr.attrdefs: U.S. Geological Survey, Woods Hole Science Center

attr.attrdef: Assigned by DSAS based on ordering of transects along the baseline. Allows user to sort transect data sequentially alongshore from baseline start to baseline end.
attr.attrdefs: U.S. Geological Survey, Woods Hole Science Center

attr.attrdef: Assigned by DSAS to indicate whether or not a DSAS-generated transect has been modified (0= auto-generated DSAS transect; 1= DSAS transect has been edited by the user).
attr.attrdefs: U.S. Geological Survey, Woods Hole Science Center

overview.eaover: The entity and attribute information provided here describe the attributes that are generated using the Digital Shoreline Analysis System version 6 software. In some cases, the attributes described in this metadata file may not exist in the dataset. It is up to the DSAS user to verify the attributes and ensure all values are populated with regard to their dataset.

digtinfo.formspec: GeoJSON is an open standard geospatial data interchange format that represents simple geographic features and their nonspatial attributes.
digtinfo.formcont: Based on JavaScript Object Notation (JSON), GeoJSON is a format for encoding a variety of geographic data structures. GeoJSON files can be converted to and from shapefiles in GIS software.
